    	<h2>Copyright &amp; Privacy Policy</h2>
        <h6>Last Updated June 18, 2014</h6>
        <br>
        <h4>Collection of Your Information</h4>
            <p>Our web server does not automatically recognize any information regarding the domain or e-mail address of visitors to our site.</p>
            <p>The Shingo Institute only stores information that you provide when registering for an event, newsletter or filling out a form through our site. The Shingo Institute does not distribute, sell, or lease member lists to third parties. The Shingo Institute may, from time to time, contact you about a particular offering, to update your member profile, or about the Shingo Institute services that may be of interest to you.</p>
            <p>This site uses Google Analytics web analytics service. Google may record mouse clicks, mouse movements, scrolling activity as well as any text you type in this website. Google does not collect personally identifiable information that you do not voluntarily enter in this website. Google does not track your browsing habits across web sites, which do not use Google services. For more information see Privacy Policy for Information Collected by the Google Analytics Service you can visit <a href="https://www.google.com/intl/en/analytics/privacyoverview.html">https://www.google.com/intl/en/analytics/privacyoverview.html</a>.</p>
        <h4>Security of Your Information</h4>
            <p>The Shingo Institute is committed to protecting the security of your information. We use a variety of security technologies and procedures to help protect your information from unauthorized access, use, or disclosure. For example, we store the personal information you provide on computer systems with limited access, which are located in a controlled facility. When we transmit highly confidential information (such as a credit card number) over the internet, we protect it through the use of 128-bit encryption, such as the Secure Socket Layer (SSL) protocol.</p>
            <p>We reveal only the last four digits of your credit card number when confirming an order. Of course, we transmit the entire credit card number to Authorize.net for order processing. After order processing we do not store your credit card information.</p>
        <h4>Use of Session Cookies</h4>
            <p>The Shingo Institute uses "session cookies" to help you personalize your online experience. A session cookie is a text file that is placed on your hard disk by a web page server. Session cookies cannot be used to run programs or deliver viruses to your computer. Session cookies are uniquely assigned to you and can only be read by a web server in the domain that issued the session cookie to you. These session cookie files disappear when you end your session. They are not stored permanently on your computer.</p>
            <p>You have the ability to accept or decline cookies. Most web browsers automatically accept cookies, but you can usually modify your browser setting to decline cookies if you prefer. If you choose to decline cookies, you may not be able to fully experience the interactive features of the The Shingo Institute services or web sites you visit.</p>
